extremeCpuUtilizationRisingTrap.name: extremeCpuUtilizationRisingTrap
extremeCpuUtilizationRisingTrap.description: CPU Utilizations Rising trap generated when extremeCpuUtilRisingThreshold is touched/crossed This trap is supported only in ExtremeWare.

extremeCpuUtilizationFallingTrap.name: extremeCpuUtilizationFallingTrap
extremeCpuUtilizationFallingTrap.description: CPU Utilization Falling Trap is generated when the extremeCpuAggregateUtilization falls below 80% of the extremeCpuUtilRisingThreshold This trap is supported only in ExtremeWare.

extremeProcessorStateChangeTrap.name: extremeProcessorStateChangeTrap
extremeProcessorStateChangeTrap.description: Failed processor on module has been detected.

extremeEsrpTimedOutFailedOverMaster.name: extremeEsrpTimedOutFailedOverMaster
extremeEsrpTimedOutFailedOverMaster.description: The master node performed a hitless MSM failover, but the master failed to resume normal operation within the reelect timeout. Thus, a new master (this switch) was elected.

extremeExceededByteCount.name: extremeExceededByteCount
extremeExceededByteCount.description: The number of bytes that exceeded the rate.

extremeBgpPrefixReachedThreshold.name: extremeBgpPrefixReachedThreshold
extremeBgpPrefixReachedThreshold.description: The extremeBgpPrefixReachedThreshold notification is generated when the number of prefixes received over this peer session reaches the threshold limit.

extremeBgpPrefixMaxExceeded.name: extremeBgpPrefixMaxExceeded
extremeBgpPrefixMaxExceeded.description: The extremeBgpPrefixMaxExceeded notification is generated when the number of prefixes received over this peer session reaches the maximum configured limit.

extremeMacLimitExceeded.name: extremeMacLimitExceeded
extremeMacLimitExceeded.description: This trap will be generated, for a port on which limit-learning has been configured, when a new MAC address exceeding the limit is learnt on that port.

extremeUnauthorizedPortForMacDetected.name: extremeUnauthorizedPortForMacDetected
extremeUnauthorizedPortForMacDetected.description: This trap will be generated when a MAC Address is learnt on a port on which it is not not authorized. This will happen when the MAC address is statically configured as a 'secure mac' on some other port(s).

extremeMacDetectedOnLockedPort.name: extremeMacDetectedOnLockedPort
extremeMacDetectedOnLockedPort.description: This trap will be generated on a port for which lock-learning has been configured, when a new MAC address is learnt on that port.

extremeMacSecurityVlanIfIndex.name: extremeMacSecurityVlanIfIndex
extremeMacSecurityVlanIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the VLAN on which the MAC address was received.

extremeMacSecurityVlanDescr.name: extremeMacSecurityVlanDescr
extremeMacSecurityVlanDescr.description: The description(name) of the VLAN on which the MAC address was received.

extremeMacSecurityPortIfIndex.name: extremeMacSecurityPortIfIndex
extremeMacSecurityPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the port on which the MAC address was received.

extremeMacSecurityVlanId.name: extremeMacSecurityVlanId
extremeMacSecurityVlanId.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN on which the MAC address was received.

extremeNetloginUserLogin.name: extremeNetloginUserLogin
extremeNetloginUserLogin.description: This trap will be generated when a netlogin supplicant passes authentication and logs in successfully into the network.

extremeNetloginUserLogout.name: extremeNetloginUserLogout
extremeNetloginUserLogout.description: This trap will be generated when a netlogin supplicant logs out. This trap is meant to notify logout event only for already authenticated and logged in supplicant.

extremeNetloginAuthFailure.name: extremeNetloginAuthFailure
extremeNetloginAuthFailure.description: This trap will be generated upon authentication failure for a netlogin supplicant

extremeGratuitousArpViolation.name: extremeGratuitousArpViolation
extremeGratuitousArpViolation.description: This trap will be generated on a valn for which gratuitous ARP protection has been configured, when a gratuitous ARP does not match the internal static or secured IP<->MAC binding.

extremeNetloginPortIfIndex.name: extremeNetloginPortIfIndex
extremeNetloginPortIfIndex.description: IfIndex of authenticator port to which the netlogin supplicant is connected

extremeNetloginAuthType.name: extremeNetloginAuthType
extremeNetloginAuthType.description: IF supplicant is authenticated using remote authentication server as RADIUS or locally using authenticator local user database

extremeNetloginSystemTime.name: extremeNetloginSystemTime
extremeNetloginSystemTime.description: The time when a netlogin event occurs and is meaningful for accounting purposes.

extremeNetloginUser.name: extremeNetloginUser
extremeNetloginUser.description: Information containing type of session as NETLOGIN or DOT1X concatenated with userName i,e '[NETLOGIN | DOT1X]:<username>'

extremeNetloginSrcVlan.name: extremeNetloginSrcVlan
extremeNetloginSrcVlan.description: Upon successful login this vlan will represent the one in which user resides before authentication while upon logout this vlan will be the one in which user resides before logout. If the user was authenticated on multiple vlans (using the Extreme-Netlogin-Extended vlan vendor specific attribute VSA 211) then this object represents the untagged vlan (if present) or the tagged vlan with the lowest tag from the extremeNetloginMoveFromVlanList.

extremeNetloginDestVlan.name: extremeNetloginDestVlan
extremeNetloginDestVlan.description: The description (name) of the VLAN in which user moves after successful login or logout. If the user was authenticated on multiple vlans (using the Extreme-Netlogin-Extended vlan vendor specific attribute VSA 211) then this object represents the untagged vlan (if present) or the tagged vlan with the lowest tag from the extremeNetloginMoveToVlanList.

extremeNetloginSessionStatus.name: extremeNetloginSessionStatus
extremeNetloginSessionStatus.description: -success (1) Successful login -sessionReset (2) Administrator has initialized Authentication State. -fDBAgingInitiatedLogout (3) Logout initiated due to FDB aging of client MAC -userInitiatedLogout(4) Graceful logout attempt from user -sessionRefreshInitiatedLogout (5) (Valid for web-based mode only) Logout initiated by session-refresh mechanism. -authenticationFailure(6) Authentication Failure -remoteAuthenticationServerFailure (7) Remote Authentication server Failure. -reauthenticationFailure (10) Dot1X reauthentication failure. -successWithRestrictedAccess (11) 802.1X supplicant will be authenticated but with restricted network access -successWithTimeLimitedAccess (12) 802.1X supplicant will be given full network access for a limited time period

extremeNetloginAuthDataBase.name: extremeNetloginAuthDataBase
extremeNetloginAuthDataBase.description: The last authentication database used by the netlogin client to get authenticated.

extremeNetloginMoveFromVlanList.name: extremeNetloginMoveFromVlanList
extremeNetloginMoveFromVlanList.description: Upon successful login extremeNetloginMoveFromVlanList will represent the vlans in which user resides before authentication and upon logout it represents the vlans in which the user resides before unauthentication.

extremeNetloginMoveToVlanList.name: extremeNetloginMoveToVlanList
extremeNetloginMoveToVlanList.description: Upon successful login extremeNetloginMoveToVlanList will represent the vlans in which user resides after authentication and upon logout it represents the vlans in which the user resides after unauthentication.

extremeArpSecurityVlanIfIndex.name: extremeArpSecurityVlanIfIndex
extremeArpSecurityVlanIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the VLAN on which the ARP packet was received.

extremeArpSecurityVlanDescr.name: extremeArpSecurityVlanDescr
extremeArpSecurityVlanDescr.description: The description(name) of the VLAN on which the ARP packet was received.

extremeArpSecurityPortIfIndex.name: extremeArpSecurityPortIfIndex
extremeArpSecurityPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the port on which the ARP packet was received.

extremeArpSecurityIpAddr.name: extremeArpSecurityIpAddr
extremeArpSecurityIpAddr.description: source IP address of the ARP packet

extremeArpSecurityMacAddress.name: extremeArpSecurityMacAddress
extremeArpSecurityMacAddress.description: source MAC address in the ARP packet

extremeNMSDeviceAddress.name: extremeNMSDeviceAddress
extremeNMSDeviceAddress.description: The IP address of the device modified by Extreme's Network Management Application.

extremeNMSInventoryChanged.name: extremeNMSInventoryChanged
extremeNMSInventoryChanged.description: This trap is sent by Extreme's Network Management Applications when a change in its inventory database occurs. This trap is not send by a router or switch.

extremeNMSTopologyChanged.name: extremeNMSTopologyChanged
extremeNMSTopologyChanged.description: This trap is sent by Extreme's Network Management Applications when a change in its Topology database occurs. This trap is not send by a router or switch.

extremeElrpVlanLoopDetected.name: extremeElrpVlanLoopDetected
extremeElrpVlanLoopDetected.description: The extremeElrpVlanLoopDetected notification is generated when the ELRP client detects a loop in the vlan.

extremeEapsStateChange.name: extremeEapsStateChange
extremeEapsStateChange.description: The extremeEapsStateChange notification is generated when the EAPS domain has a state change.

extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagSet.name: extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagSet
extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagSet.description: The extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagSet notification is generated when the EAPS domain's fail timer expires for the first time, while its state is not in Fail state.

extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagClear.name: extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagClear
extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagClear.description: The extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagClear notification is generated when the EAPS domain's Fail timer expired flag is cleared.

extremeEapsLinkDownRingComplete.name: extremeEapsLinkDownRingComplete
extremeEapsLinkDownRingComplete.description: If a Transit is in Link-Down state, and it receives a Health-Check-Pdu from the Master indicating the ring is Complete, it means there is some problem with the Transit switch that has issued this trap message.

extremeEapsPortStatusChange.name: extremeEapsPortStatusChange
extremeEapsPortStatusChange.description: The extremeEapsPortStatusChange notification is generated when an EAPS primary or secondary port changes state.

extremeEapsConfigChange.name: extremeEapsConfigChange
extremeEapsConfigChange.description: The extremeEapsConfigChange notification is generated when the EAPS configuration has changed. It is sent 30 seconds after the first change is made to limit the number of traps sent

extremeEapsLastStatusChangeTime.name: extremeEapsLastStatusChangeTime
extremeEapsLastStatusChangeTime.description: The extremeEapsLastStatusChangeTime notification is generated 10 seconds after a status change occurs. Within the 10 second period all status changes cause extremeEapsLastStatusChange variable to be updated. 10 seconds after the first change, this trap is sent. This is to ensure a management station is notified that a change occured, in case the regular traps are dropped due to be being sent while the network is converging.

extremeBgpM2PrefixReachedThreshold.name: extremeBgpM2PrefixReachedThreshold
extremeBgpM2PrefixReachedThreshold.description: The extremeBgpPrefixReachedThreshold notification is generated when the number of prefixes received over this peer session reaches the threshold limit.

extremeBgpM2PrefixMaxExceeded.name: extremeBgpM2PrefixMaxExceeded
extremeBgpM2PrefixMaxExceeded.description: The extremeBgpPrefixMaxExceeded notification is generated when the number of prefixes received over this peer session reaches the maximum configured limit.

extremePethPSUStatusNotification.name: extremePethPSUStatusNotification
extremePethPSUStatusNotification.description: This Notification indicates a change in the PoE PSU for the slot.

extremeSegmentPort.name: extremeSegmentPort
extremeSegmentPort.description: The EAPS Shared Link's Segment Id.

extremeSharedPort.name: extremeSharedPort
extremeSharedPort.description: The EAPS Shared Link's Shared port.

extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagSet.name: extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagSet
extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagSet.description: The extremeEapsFailTimerExpFlagSet notification is generated when the EAPS domain's segment timer expires for the first time.

extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagClear.name: extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagClear
extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagClear.description: The extremeEapsSegmentTimerExpFlagClear notification is generated when the EAPS domain's Segment Fail timer expired flag is cleared.

extremeEapsSharedPortStateChange.name: extremeEapsSharedPortStateChange
extremeEapsSharedPortStateChange.description: The extremeEapsSharedPortStateChange notification is generated when the EAPS shared port state changes.

extremeEapsRootBlockerStatusChange.name: extremeEapsRootBlockerStatusChange
extremeEapsRootBlockerStatusChange.description: The extremeEapsSharedPortRootBlockerChange notification is generated when each switch detects a new rootblocker ID on the networks.

extremeLacpAddPortToAggregator.name: extremeLacpAddPortToAggregator
extremeLacpAddPortToAggregator.description: This Notification indicates when a LACP member-port has been added to the Aggregator.

extremeLacpDeletePortFromAggregator.name: extremeLacpDeletePortFromAggregator
extremeLacpDeletePortFromAggregator.description: This Notification indicates when a LACP member-port has been deleted from the Aggregator.

extremeOverheat.name: extremeOverheat
extremeOverheat.description: A overheat trap indicates that the on board tempature sensor has reported a overheat condition. System will shutdown until unit has sufficiently cooled such that operation may begin again. A cold start trap will be issued when the unit has come back on line.

extremeFanfailed.name: extremeFanfailed
extremeFanfailed.description: A fan failed trap indicates one or more of the cooling fans inside the device has failed. A fanOK trap will be sent once the fan has attained normal operation.

extremeFanOK.name: extremeFanOK
extremeFanOK.description: A fan has transitioned out of a failure state and is now operating correctly.

extremeInvalidLoginAttempt.name: extremeInvalidLoginAttempt
extremeInvalidLoginAttempt.description: A user attempted to login to console or by telnet but was refused access due to incorrect username or password

extremePowerSupplyFail.name: extremePowerSupplyFail
extremePowerSupplyFail.description: One or more sources of power to this agent has failed. Presumably a redundant power-supply has taken over.

extremePowerSupplyGood.name: extremePowerSupplyGood
extremePowerSupplyGood.description: One or more previously bad sources of power to this agent has come back to life without causing an agent restart.

extremeSmartTrap.name: extremeSmartTrap
extremeSmartTrap.description: Signifies that the value of one of the object identifiers (or the value of an object below that in the MIB tree) defined in the extremeSmartTrapRulesTable has changed, and hence a new entry has been created in the extremeSmartTrapInstanceTable. Such a trap is sent at most once every thirty seconds if one or more entry was created in the last thirty seconds.

extremeModuleStateChanged.name: extremeModuleStateChanged
extremeModuleStateChanged.description: Signifies that the value of the extremeSlotModuleState for the specified extremeSlotNumber has changed. Traps will be reported only for significant states.

extremeEdpNeighborAdded.name: extremeEdpNeighborAdded
extremeEdpNeighborAdded.description: This node discovers a new neighbor through Extreme Discovery Protocol.

extremeEdpNeighborRemoved.name: extremeEdpNeighborRemoved
extremeEdpNeighborRemoved.description: No EDP updates are received from this neighbor within the configured timeout period and this neighbor entry is aged out by the device.
